{
    "level": "A1–A2",
    "intro": "The patterns <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> show that <strong>something exists</strong> or <strong>does not exist</strong> in a place.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Singular",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "For <strong>one</strong> thing, use <strong>there is</strong>.",
            "example": "There is a lamp on the desk."
        },
        {
            "label": "Plural",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "For <strong>more than one</strong> thing, use <strong>there are</strong>.",
            "example": "There are two cups in the kitchen."
        },
        {
            "label": "Negative / Question",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "Add <strong>not</strong> or move <strong>is / are</strong> forward to make a question.",
            "example": "There isn't a chair here. / Is there a shop nearby?"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Main patterns",
    "intro": "First choose: one thing or more than one.",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Affirmative",
            "title": "There is + singular",
            "subtitle": "There is a cat in the garden."
        },
        {
            "label": "Affirmative",
            "title": "There are + plural",
            "subtitle": "There are three books on the shelf."
        },
        {
            "label": "Negative",
            "title": "There isn't / There aren't",
            "subtitle": "There isn't a key here. / There aren't any buses now."
        },
        {
            "label": "Question",
            "title": "Is there ...? / Are there ...?",
            "subtitle": "Is there a bank nearby? / Are there any chairs?"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Where this is useful",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "In a room / house",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Describe what is in a room, on a table, in a bag, or at home.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "There is a sofa in the living room.",
                    "ua": "There is a sofa in the living room."
                },
                {
                    "en": "There are clean plates in the cupboard.",
                    "ua": "There are clean plates in the cupboard."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "With any in negatives and questions",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "In negatives and questions, <strong>any</strong> is often used.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "There isn't any milk in the fridge.",
                    "ua": "There isn't any milk in the fridge."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Are there any students in the classroom?",
                    "ua": "Are there any students in the classroom?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Short answers",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "In short answers, repeat <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Is there a pharmacy here? — Yes, there is.",
                    "ua": "Is there a pharmacy here? — Yes, there is."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Are there any tickets? — No, there aren't.",
                    "ua": "Are there any tickets? — No, there aren't."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Singular vs plural",
    "intro": "See how the pattern changes from one thing to more than one.",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "There is a chair in the room.",
            "ua": "One thing",
            "note": "is + singular noun"
        },
        {
            "en": "There are two chairs in the room.",
            "ua": "More than one thing",
            "note": "are + plural noun"
        },
        {
            "en": "Is there a chair in the room?",
            "ua": "Question",
            "note": "is before there"
        },
        {
            "en": "Are there two chairs in the room?",
            "ua": "Question",
            "note": "are before there"
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Do not say <strong>There are a chair</strong> or <strong>There is two chairs</strong>."
}

{
    "title": "4. Common mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Mistake 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Using are with a singular noun.",
            "wrong": "❌ There are a lamp on the table.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">There is a lamp on the table.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Using is with a plural noun.",
            "wrong": "❌ There is two shops nearby.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">There are two shops nearby.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Mixing there is with it is.",
            "wrong": "❌ It is a book on the desk.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">There is a book on the desk.</span>"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Short summary",
    "items": [
        "<strong>There is</strong> = one thing.",
        "<strong>There are</strong> = more than one thing or person.",
        "Negative: <strong>there isn't</strong> / <strong>there aren't</strong>.",
        "Question: <strong>Is there...?</strong> / <strong>Are there...?</strong>",
        "Use the pattern with <strong>there</strong> when you talk about existence in a place."
    ]
}

